Type Categorization
Python utilizes dynamic runtime type interpretation. Use the implicit types structurally:

name = "Harry"          # String (str)
age = 25                # Integer (int)
price = 99.99           # Float (float)
is_active = True        # Boolean (bool)

# Multiple Assignments
x, y = 10, 20
a = b = c = 0

# Constant Conventions (Developer Enforced)
PI = 3.14
MAX_SIZE = 100

Evaluation & Type Checking:
x = 5
print(type(x))             # Output: <class 'int'>
print(isinstance(x, int))  # Output: True
